      Product description

      Description Ugreen 40234 HDMI 3×1 switcher provides a way to switch among multiple HDMI sources, like Laptop, HD-DVD, PS3, Xbox360 to a HDMI TV or display. It allows the switching of 3 inputs and maintains all signal components present within the encoded signal HDCP encryption. You could easily select from different programme sources via front panel push buttons or IR remote control without moving cables around. Specification 1. Support 4K*2K@30Hz, Full HD 1080P; 2. Support 3D; 3. Support 12-bit per channel(36bit all channel) deep color; 4. Supports 250MHz/2.5Gbps per channel (7.5Gbps all channel); 5. No external power supply required; 6. Switching: key-press-switching, IR remote control; 7. Size: 126*75*18mm. Package Contents Ugreen 40234 HDMI Switcher 3 to 1 ×1; IR Remote ×1; Mannual×1; Warranty Card×1.

      Note
      1. Suggest using HDMI 1.4 and HDMI 2.0 cable as input cable.
      2. Suggest input HDMI cable less than or equal to 15ft, output HDMI cable less than or equal to 30ft.
      3. There is a plastic film in the battery slot of the remote, please remove it firstly before using the remote.

      Product Description

      UGREEN HDMI Switch 4K 3 Port HDMI Switcher Splitter Hub 4K Full HD 1080P 3D Compatible for PC Laptop, Xbox 360 One, PS4 PS3, Nintendo Switch

      Widely Compatible

      Support HDMI Standard source such as XBOX, PS3, PS4, Blu-ray, DVD player, Apple TV, TV Box, PC, Laptop,etc.

      Output to HDMI standard display such a Monitor, HDTV, Projectors, etc.

      Seamless Auto Switch

      The HDMI switch box allows you to input 3 HDMI source device to 1 TV/Display/Monitor.

      HDMI switcher will automatically switch to the latest detected HDMI source seamlessly.

      Save you trouble to switch your display to your latest HDMI device.

      • Note:
      • Please use HDMI cable with HDMI 1.4 version or Above for best performance.
      • The input cable should not be longer than 5m, the output cable should not be longer than 10m, otherwaise, signal will decrease.

      4K Output

      The HDMI Switch support 4K video output through the cables to allow you capture more detail.

      Plug&Play, Easy Set-up

      Simply plug in the HDMI inputs and output as well as the IR Receiver, the micro USB cable is used for power supply for max performance

      More Fun Sharing with Friends

      Makes it so much easy to switch between different devices to enjoy fun time with your families and friends

      Read more

      Remotely Switch at Your Will

      The IR Remote Controller that allows you to switch between 3 HDMI source wirelessly.

      There's a manual button on the HDMI Switch BOX for channel switch by press on it.

      Note:

      1. Please pull off the plastic clip from the remote controller before using.
      2. The distance should be within 5m with NO barrier.

      Specification

      1. Support 4K*2K, Full HD 1080P

      2. Support 3D

      3. Support 12-bit per channel (36bit all channel) deep color

      4. Supports 250MHz/2.5Gbps per channel (7.5Gbps all channel)

      5. No external power supply required

      6. Switching: key-press-switching, IR remote control

      7. Size: 126*75*18mm

      Ben Stein
      1.0 out of 5 stars Mine was defective, hope yours isn't.
      Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2018
      Verified Purchase
      I grew to like the way the thing is designed generally. At first the lack of a power supply was disappointing, but then I realized the supplied micro-USB power cord could plug into the otherwise-useless USB power port on a nearby power strip. At first the IR setup was a little confusing (you have to plug the sensor in), but the instructions cleared that up, and that bit worked fine. It switched reliably and the physical design is attractive.

      I can't forgive the quality control problem, though. The unit I received absolutely could not support 4k 30Hz output from my Roku (TV would lose signal altogether when the Roku flipped to 4k), nor could it even maintain 1080p from my Tivo (frequent video/audio drop-outs). I spent time and money blaming other things, but it really did prove to be the switch. Manufacturers should implement enough quality assurance to ensure that defects in this kind of product are super-rare. UGREEN wasted a ton of my time.

      Moving on now to try the "ViewHD Prosumer 4k" switch, which literally claims to be "THE BEST HDMI v2.0 4x1 Switch on earth." We'll see!

      J. Herian-Phat
      5.0 out of 5 stars Best option for a cheap and effective switcher.
      Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2017
      Verified Purchase
      I'd spent about a week trying to find a decent switcher that could work well with my game consoles after seeing that quite a few people had issues with the more popular choices so I settled on this one because of its price and good design. Much to my surprise it worked better than expected. For a Sony Bravia tv, PS4's and PS3's are still linked to the tv through the switch so auto turn on and tv remote functions still work. I don't have a 4k tv so I can't test if it really outputs 4k, but I haven't had any issues with 1080p video and everything runs perfect. Some people claimed in other reviews that this switch does not come with a charger which is completely false. It may just be a USB cable, but for my setup I have it plugged into my tv USB port and it runs fine. My only complaint would be that the IR sensor is a separate piece that plugs into the switch. Overall if you're looking for a cheap switcher and not too worried about future proofing your setup I'd recommend this one.

      4.0 out of 5 stars Great product and does what it says.
      Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2018
      Verified Purchase
      We just hooked this up today. So far, we are very pleased with the product. It does exactly what it is advertised to do. My only complaints (which are very minor) are the following. The buttons on the remote are in a diamond pattern with the top button being button 1, the left being 2 and the right being 3. Like I said, not a big deal but if you like things to be in order, this may bother you too. The second issue has not led to any issue but I suppose it could. The device comes with a micro USB power cable but does not come with a wall plug to accommodate the USB plug. The instructions state that this plug is not even necessary unless one of the devices plugged into the switch requires a lot of power. We didn't plug it in and everything is working fine. However, if we ever need it, we will have to purchase that independently. These two issues are the only reason I didn't give it 5 stars and like I said, these are very minor issues.
